ator><![CDATA[angelinesg7]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>These colors don’t run. Or do they?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/3AEJDrV</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/q2c7AvS.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4XwTie2.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/3AEJDrV</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ADegenFromUpcountry]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Terry Crews is the man</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/zyXezvc</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/wuHey73.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/zyXezvc</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mike0xsmall]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>My journey to good mental health and well-being</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/eYFLgxT</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/xxfeGkz.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is me in 2017. I was 46 and 25 stone (350lbs/159kgs at 5'10/178cm). I was really unhappy. I remember that day really well. I felt incredibly self-conscious and full of self-loathing and shame. I was trying to enjoy a day out with my lovely son but I was only too aware of some of the judgmental glances I got from other diners which tainted my enjoyment. 

At the time I was sharing a home with my ex-husband. Looking back I don't know why I agreed to live like this. But my ex told me we couldn't afford for us to live separately so I went along with his plan. This had been my problem. Not having my own voice. Not having the confidence to live my life as I wished. My married had been unhappy because of this imbalance of power. 

But I reached a limit and realised that I could just move out anyway. There was a lot of gaslighting from my ex. This took the form of him saying I would be a huge financial burden to him as I couldn't manage my own finances as I was a "spendthrift". But eventually I  moved out anyway. I started  renting my own place 3 years ago almost to the day. I had the good fortune to rent a lovely semi-detached cottage on a farm by a beautiful forest that leads down to a often deserted beach. Having my own space with access to beautiful outdoor space gave me the tools I needed to start improving my mental health and addressing the issues that were either the cause of, or the symptoms of, my mental health issues. 

I started to walk a lot. Miles and miles in the woods. It took some time to find the mental strength to address my comfort eating but last year I underwent a lifestyle overhaul that really changed everything. I cut out sugar and carbs and ate healthily. My weight started to go down and my mental health improved. 

This year I got a part-time job and in April I started doing crossfit 3 times a week. I haven't felt this well and calm in own skin in my whole life. I like who I see in the mirror. I'm proud of my strong, fit body. Which is getting stronger and fitter every week.  

I've lost weight before but this time I made the focus health (mental and physical) and well-being rather than being as skinny as possible. That change of focus changed the game completely. 

At 51 I've never felt better and I'm excited for the future.  To any other unhappy middle-aged people out there find what motivates you and make that first step to changing your life. It's never too late to change everything.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mmjghjF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>From a size 26 to a size 16 ?</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hXS8Eou.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Me now

Thank you so so much to all the lovely imgurians who have commented on my post. I love this community so much. I have been inspired by many stories shared on this site and I hope my story inspires others to turn that shit around and turn it into pure fucking gold. xxx</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/eYFLgxT</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[CazzaMcSpazza]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>III</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/bcrHOuP</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/y727JJu.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bcrHOuP</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[lpooptoomuch]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>1989 Germany, pilot lands a plane on a field so it can be placed at the museum nearby. Its cheaper then transporting it for sure.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/KdBfq1U</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lUHT6QQ.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/KdBfq1U</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[funkystay]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>germs confused</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/gmZKemi</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/t3G3biS.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/gmZKemi</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[codrcrew]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Make up a bunch of these and sneak them into Home Depot</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/mAN68VJ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ikMa4am.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HMJ1vNY.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pQMA9Ni.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height